[P]AMD Ryzen 7 3800X 8-Core (Matisse) 3.90GHz [MTS-B0] ASRock B450 Steel Legend BIOS P4.30 02/25/2022 Serial M80-F9006900482

  Описание   Память Частота 1200.01 MHz                [_]Write          Default                Draco Dormiens Nunquam Titillandus

  DDR4 RAM CAS Латентность (tCL)         |>|13.33 ns   [>]16[^]1-31      [>]16[^]1-31      |R|  Tweaking the memory timing is likely to cause
  Задержка RAS -> CAS (tRCD)             |>|13.33 ns   [>]16[^]1-31      [>]16[^]1-31      |R|  system instability and you do this entirely
  Презаряд RAS (tRP)                     |>|13.33 ns   [>]16[^]1-31      [>]16[^]1-31      |R|  at your own risk. I wish you Good Luck! 😱
  Время цикла (tRAS)                     |>|32.50 ns   [>]39[^]1-63      [>]39[^]1-63      |A|  To enable [ Apply ] specify the -TWEAK command qualifier.
  Время цикла банка (tRC)                |>|45.83 ns   [>]55[^]1-95      [>]55[^]1-95      |G|  I expect this panel to be mainly used to setup
  Время цикла обновления строки (tRFC)   |>|350.83 ns  [>]421[^]64-1023  [>]421[^]64-1023  |G|  the defaults for memory timings highlighting.

Setup the revised timings then press [ Apply ] to write them to the Ryzen 7 (K17) memory controller registers.

#    Power Scheme Имя             Power Scheme Описание

[0]  |C|Home/Office Desk          This scheme is suited to most home or desktop computers that are left plugged in all the time.
[1]     Portable/Laptop           This scheme is designed for extended battery life for portable computers on the road.
[2]     Presentation              This scheme keeps the monitor on for doing presentations.
[3]     Always On                 This scheme keeps the computer running so that it can be accessed from the network.
                                  Use this scheme if you do not have network wakeup hardware.
[4]     Minimal Power Management  This scheme keeps the computer on and optimizes it for high performance.
[5]     Max Battery               This scheme is extremely aggressive for saving power.

             [_]-ADAPTERS          Show [Adapters] on the initial screen
             [_]-AIOCTL            Enable automatic AIO Link Control (Corsair + NZXT)
             [_]-AIOLED            Enable DIMM LED Reporting and Control (Corsair)
             [_]-NOBALLOON         Disable the display of Balloon Tooltips
             [_]-BLUE              Show [Bluetooth] on the initial screen
             [_]-BOINC             On startup display the [BOINC Status] panel
             [_]-DELAY=2           Delay the SIV64X start-up by 2 seconds
             [_]-DXD               Load DirectX Root Child Details
             [_]-NOECR             Disable Embedded Controller Reporting
             [_]-FREE              Show <free> unused USB Root Hub ports on [USB Bus]
             [_]-GPUCTL            Enable GPU Fan Control and Overclocking
             [_]-INDENT            Indent [Buttons] to reflect hierarchy on [USB Bus]
             [_]-LOCAL             Limit SIV64X to the local system
             [_]-NOLCD             Disable use of LCD Panel Displays
             [_]-NOLINK            Disable use of AIO Link Hardware (Aqua + Corsair + NZXT)
             [_]-NOMBS             Use Technical rather thean Marketing descriptions
             [_]-PRIORITY=ABOVE    Force the SIV64X Base Priority Class to Above Normal
             [_]-SINGLE            Only allow a single instance of SIV64X to be active
             [_]-NOTHEME           Disable use of Windows Themes on XP and later
             [_]-TRAY              Start SIV64X minimised in the Icon Tray
             [_]-WDF               Enable the Windows Driver Framework (WDF) pages
             [_]-NOWIZARD          Disable the Wizard Cursors

             Use this panel to setup the SIV64X Default Command Qualifiers that will be used when
             none are specified on the command line. Press [Save] to write them to the registry.
             These will be used when SIV64X is next started and the [About] panel will report them.
